                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.6363/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-31T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1921—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your No. 20 March 8, 6 P.M.</p>
                <p>Information sent by Johnston has been circulated confidentially to oil companies.
                    Department desires further information regarding Siak concessions and splitting
                    of Djambi area. These appear to be <pb facs="0630" n="534" xml:id="pg_534"/>
                    separate propositions. Are you in touch with Standard Oil representative at The
                    Hague? Is there not danger of creating a situation where one American company
                    will be played off against another? Van der Woude has been asked to call at
                    Department. Whole situation requires clarifying. Give Department your views.
                    Inform Johnston.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
